    <activity>
      <!--<title> Scalar Multiplication and Vector Addition </title>-->
      <introduction>
      <p>
    Suppose that
    <me>
      \vvec = \left[\begin{array}{r} 3 \\ 1 \end{array}
      \right],
      \wvec = \left[\begin{array}{r} -1 \\ 2 \end{array}
      \right].
    </me>
      </p></introduction>
     
   
      <task> <p> Find expressions for the vectors
      <me>
        \begin{array}{cccc}
        \vvec, \amp 2\vvec, \amp -\vvec, \amp -2\vvec, \\
        \wvec, \amp 2\wvec, \amp -\wvec, \amp -2\wvec\text{.} \\
        \end{array}
      </me>
      and sketch them in the <m>xy</m> plane.

    </p> </task>

    <task> <p> What geometric effect does scalar multiplication by a positive number have
    on a vector?  (A) preserves the length, changes the direction, (B) preserves the direction, changes the length, (C) changes the length and the direction.
    </p></task>

    <task> <p> What geometric effect does scalar multiplication by a negative number have
    on a vector?  (A) preserves the length, changes the direction, (B) preserves the direction, changes the length, (C) changes the length and the direction.
    </p></task>
  </activity>

